inn1.comm: good length delivery angling into Cook who pushes forward and defends straight past Zaheer, the ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end
defended on the back foot towards Zaheer, he isn't up to full speed as yet, warming up in the cold conditions
strays on to the pads and Cook gets off the mark by flicking the ball down to fine leg
good length delivery pitches on off and angles across the right-hander, defended towards cover on the front foot
defended to mid-off on the front foot
short of  a length on leg stump, Prior moves across and tucks the ball off his hips towards fine leg, he gets off the mark with a double
full ball on middle and off stump, Cook leans forward and defends towards cover point
good length delivery on middle stump, Cook comes on to the front foot and defends solidly back to Agarkar
good length once again on middle and off stump, Cook waits on the back foot and defends towards point
good length delivery outside off, Cook gets on to the back foot and lets the ball go through to Dhoni
slightly fuller in length on off stump, Cook strides forward and drives firmly to Tendulkar at mid-off
short of a length on leg stump, Cook whips it off his pads in front of square, Piyush Chawla gives chase and pulls it in just inside the boundary
good length delivery on off and middle stump, defended on the back foot towards Zaheer
defended on the back foot towards Zaheer once again
fuller ball on off stump, Cook defends on the front foot towards mid-on, sedate start by England, nothing's really happened yet
tight line and length around off stump, Cook pushes the ball towards cover
short of a length outside off, Cook plays it with soft hands in front of cover and scampers through for a single

short of  a length outside off stump, Prior waits for it on the back foot and drives into the gap at cover, he didn't hit that hard, just timed it well, Yuvraj gives chase and keeps the batsmen down to three
short ball outside off stump, Prior gets under it and cuts it down to third man
width offered outside the off stump, Cook stands on the back foot and drives through cover for four, nicely timed and the placement was perfect, the pitch is doing nothing, very benign
defended on the back foot towards midwicket
full toss on off stump, Cook leans forward and drives to mid-off
Cook tries to force the drive through cover but mis-times it to mid-on instead
another full toss but Cook misses out on an easy scoring chance by hitting it straight to extra cover
Prior moves across his stumps and tries to flick, he misses and gets hit on the pad, Zaheer appeals but isn't joined by anyone else for the ball pitched outside leg stump
short of  a length and that bounced a bit more than Cook expected, he tried to drive the ball through the off side but was cramped for room and got beaten
flicked off the pads to midwicket
defended on the back foot to the off side
good length delivery angling into Cook who waits on the back foot and tries to flick, he misses and gets hit on the pad
Cook misses the flick once again and is hit on the pad, the ball was missing leg stump though
Prior tries to pull one from outside off stump but the length isn't short enough, he ends up pulling it to mid-on
driven to cover off the back foot
Prior takes one hand off the handle as he tries to drive the ball through cover, he's been cramped for room

width offered this time and Prior cuts it hard at Yuvraj at point who dives forward and tries to catch it, the ball falls short of him and hits him hard on the hand, he's in quite a lot of pain and the cold only makees it worse
fuller ball closer to off stump, defended on the front foot
Agarkar completes a maiden over by bowling one on a good length outside off, Prior defends towards cover
full delivery angling into Cook's middle stump, Cook leans forward and closes the face to play the ball to midwicket
defended off the pads to square leg
too straight from Zaheer, Cook waits on the back foot and flicks off his pads to deep midwicket
short of a length on middle and off stump, defended on the back foot to point
played with an open face towards third man, the batsmen run the first hard and put pressure on Agarkar who over-runs the ball and concedes the extra run
defended on the front foot towards mid-off
pitches outside leg stump, that's a poor line, Cook moves across his stumps and flicks the ball to the fine-leg boundary
too short and too wide outside off stump, Cook leans forward and drives through the line through cover, three more, excellent start to the over for England
Prior moves towards the off side and flicks a delivery that is angling into middle and leg stump towards fine leg
good length delivery on middle and off stump, Prior strides forward and defends towards cover
fuller delivery on middle stump, Prior pushes it wide of the fielder at mid-on for a single

pitches outside off stump and moves a fraction away from Cook who tries to cover drive without moving his feet, the ball beats the outside edge, ten runs off the over, the most expensive one of the day
good length delivery on off and middle stump, defended on the front foot towards midwicket
good length delivery on off stump, pushed towards point off the back foot
what a shot! The length wasn't too bad but Prior made room by backing away towards leg side and lofted Zaheer high and far back over his head, massive six
Zaheer comes back well by pitching on off stump and cutting the ball back into Prior and threading the gap between bat and body
defended on the front foot towards midwicket
good length ball on middle stump, Prior leans forward and defends to the leg side
good length delivery on off stump, Cook leans forward and defends
RP Singh strays down leg side, that is the first wide of the day
strays on to leg stump once again, Cook flicks off his hips down to fine leg
good length delivery pitches on middle and angles across Prior who plays from his crease and defends
Prior begins to step down the track but seeing that the length is good from RP Singh he ends up defending the ball to Uthappa at point
flicked off the pads down to fine leg for a single
good length delivery on off stump, Cook strides forward and defends towards cover
to far down the leg side, wide called
well bowled, nips across the right hander and Prior pushed at it with static footwork
pushed into the covers, there is confusion over whether they want a single, in the end Cook goes back at the non-striker's end as the throw knocks the bat out of his hand
comes at the bowler, who drags his length back and Prior can only push the ball towards mid off and scamper a single
outside edge, forcing off the back foot and it flies down to third man
there's the first wicket, Prior trying to whip the ball over the on side and gets a leading edge high towards mid-on, where Dravid takes a comfortable catch
outside off stump and Cook lets it go through...successful over for Zaheer
good length, angling across Bell who shoulders arms to his first ball
played from the crease, driven back to RP Singh in his follow-through
pushed off the back foot to backward point
Bell is away, angled down to third man in typical one-day style
back of a length and Cook turns it into the on side as square leg comes around to field, but can't collect the ball cleanly
going across Bell, who tries to cut square through the off side but doesn't make contact
cramping Cook for room, who pushes back to Agarkar...England not finding it easy, despite good batting conditions
flicked off the legs, but picks out square leg
on off stump, Cook plays towards the on side but again doesn't find a gap as mid on fields

nicely punched off the back foot, and with plenty of timing, as it beats mid off and cover and runs over the outfield with the fielder unable to chase it down...just England's third four of the innings
in defence this time, into the off side
straying onto leg stump and turned through square leg...long leg does the fielding as Cook comes back for two
third man comes into action again as Bell gets off strike
brings Cook onto the front foot and he plays and misses as the ball holds its line outside off stump
takes the pad behind square on the leg side
top shot, played on the rise through the covers as Bell registers his first boundary...that shot was all about timing and placement
brings his line closer to Bell, who defends back to RP Singh
hint of width, but Bell can't beat Yuvraj at backward point
pushed towards mid-on and it's a well-judged single from Cook
waits for the ball and uses his wrists to guide it to third man
on leg stump and turned past mid-on with enough force for him to come back for a couple
better line, on off stump and Cook can only force up to mid-off
slightly fuller, Cook comes onto the front foot and again picks out mid-off
turned into the on side, mid-on has to run to his left so there is time for Cook to pick up a single and keep the strike
swing and miss from Cook as RP Singh goes slightly wider, successfully tempting the drive
bisects midwicket and square-leg with a well-timed flick which nearly makes it to the boundary
played out to backward point, one bounce to Yuvraj
nudged to midwicket, Karthik is a little slow to react and can't prevent the single
outside off stump, Cook middles a drive but hits it straight at extra cover
top delivery, comes back into Cook off the pitch and goes between bat and pad, missing the stumps by a fraction as Dhoni takes very low...and that's drinks
turned to midwicket
finds the gap past midwicket this time, but deep square-leg runs around to prevent a boundary
comes forward, inside edge into the leg side
on the stumps, Cook whips it towards mid-on
turned off the pads out to deep square-leg, enough time for Cook to make it back for two as his score ticks over, but not at an alarming rate for the Indians
pushed into the covers, decent start from Ganguly and England are missing a trick by not attacking more
on leg stump, Bell doesn't connect and the ball dribbles into the leg side
drags this in short, Bell is quickly onto the pull but picks out midwicket
tries to cut through the off side, but takes the bottom edge and bounces in front of Dhoni
very full outside off stump, but Cook can't find a gap in a tight ring field set by Dravid
Cook tries to invent this time, coming across his stumps and making the ball a low full toss but finds midwicket
good over from Singh, Cook finds square cover with a drive and England's run rate drops back to four-an-over
short and wide, cut away but straight at Yuvraj
angled down to third man
another dot ball for Cook, turned to midwicket and the pressure is really building
scores this time, but just a single out to deep square-leg...only five boundaries so far for England
that's more like it, too short from Ganguly and Bell goes in the air over midwicket, a couple of bounces it crosses the boundary at deep midwicket
nicely played, dabbed down to third man and Bell keeps the strike
defended from middle and leg back to the bowler
pitched up, driven firmly to mid-on
looses his line, wide outside off stump and Bell latches onto it with a sweetly time cut shot between backward point and square cover
goes for the yorker, Bell digs it out into the off side and takes off for a quick single
turned towards mid-on, Bell is nearly sold a dummy by Cook as he hints at coming for a single but makes it back easily enough
that's good from Cook, drifts onto leg stump and put away past mid-on as he moves into the 40s and England end the Powerplays in positive style
good length ball on off stump, Bell leans forward and drives towards long-on
defended on the front foot towards cover
short of a length on leg stump, Cook waits on the back foot and flicks through midwicket for two more
driven firmly off the back foot towards cover
Ganguly strays on to leg stump once again, Cook flicks off his pads towards fine leg
good length delivery on off stump, driven uppishly on the front foot towards point
starts off with the googly, bowled quicker through the air outside of stump, Cook leans forward in defence and gets beaten
Cook tries to cut off the back foot and gets beaten once again
that was pre-meditated from Cook but he makes contact with the sweep and gets a single to short fine leg, that brings up the 50-run stand between these two
Bell moves down the pitch and drives firmly back at the bowler
Bell waits on the back foot and drives in front of point for one more
flatter delivery on off stump, Cook makes room and drives through cover point for  a single
good length ball on middle stump, played off the pads wide of midwicket for a single
short of a length outside off, Bell waits on the back foot and cuts the ball to third man
good length delivery but Ganguly's gentle pace allows Cook to moves back and across and flick it from middle stump through midwicket
nudged down to third man for another single
he gets his fifty but in not the most convincing fashion, Cook was early on the shot and ends up chipping it uppishly into the vacant mid-on region, well played, that's his maiden ODI fifty
defended back to the bowler
pre-meditated once again, Cook moves across his stumps and sweeps Chawla towards fine leg
quicker delivery on off stump, Bell takes a step down the pitch and drives back at Chawla
driven off the back foot through cover point for a single
flighted delivery on off and middle stump, a bit too full in length and Cook drives the ball firmly to Tendulkar at long-on
tossed up on off stump, Bell defends on the front foot towards point
driven back to the bowler on the front foot
width offered outside off stump, Cook cuts to the fielder on the point boundary
good length but the line is down leg side, Bell tries to pull it away but misses
driven off the back foot to long-off for a single
Bell tries to play a half-flick, half-pull, he didn't make contact but the impact on the pad indicated that the ball would have missed leg stump
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
quicker delivery outside off to finish the over, Cook cuts towards point
Bell tries to cut a short and wide ball through point but misses
chipped in the air but wide of midwicket for a single
flatter through the air on middle stump, Cook waits on the back foot and defends to midwicket
Cook takes on Chawla with success, the line was on off stump but Cook knelt down on one knee and slog-swept Chawla over midwicket
swepte behidn square for one more
Bell makes room by backing away and drives through extra cover off the back foot
too short and on middle and leg stump as well, Bell swivels and lofts it down to the deep backward square leg boundary, that was easy
quicker delivery on off and middle, Bell drives to long-on off the back foot
too short on leg once again, Cook moves on to the back foot and flicks to deep midwicket
Bell waits on the back foot and cuts to the fielder at short third man
defended on the back foot to midwicket
Bell leans forward and drives a fullish delivery to long-on for the seventh run of the over
tossed up on off and middle stump, Bell moves back and drives to long-on
Cook leans forward, defends with soft hands towards point and calls for the single
lovely shot, Bell nimbly skips down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and with a full swing of the amrs, sends the ball soaring over the straight boundary, that was beautiful to watch
driven off the back foot through covers for a single, that was the googly but a bit too short
defended on the back foot towards Karthik at midwicket
Bell waits on the back foot and cuts to short third man
a fraction short and Cook tries to pull it away, he didn't time it well but will get two runs towards midwicket
driven on the back foot to long-on
too short outside the off stump, Bell waits for the ball to come to him and cuts to deep point
a fraction too short on off once again, Bell opens the face to guide the ball to short third man
poor line on leg stump, fine leg is on the circle and you can't afford to bowl such a line, Bell reaches his fifty off just 54 balls by flicking of his pads to the long-leg boundary
defended to midwicket on the front foot
full ball on middle stump, flicked off the pads through square leg
cut off the back foot towards backward point
Bell come sdown the track and chips the ball high in the air, the fielder at long-on runs in but the ball falls short of him
defended towards the leg side
defended on the front foot towards midwicket
strays on to middle and leg stump, flicked off the pads to deep midwicket
round the wicket, tucked into the leg side
skids through a little as Bell works into the vacant leg side area and Yuvraj has to do the chasing to midwicket
tickled very fine past the wicketkeeper, short fine-leg races after it as the batsmen come back for three
cut off the back foot through the covers, the sweeper does the fielding
flat outside off stump, Cook carves out to deep cover
again worked through the leg side, no one inside the ring in front of the batsmen and good running brings two
leans forward and drives down to long off
touch short, stays in the crease and pushed down to long on
tries to go through the leg side, doesn't connect and takes the pad
floated up under Cook's eyes, dug out into the off side
flatter ball, outside off and chopped through the covers
quicker ball, Bell picks it and rocks onto the back foot to powerfully pull the ball over midwicket and Karthik can't stop the boundary
turned with the wrists through midwicket
goes for the reverse sweep, an appeal but Doctrove isn't interested
chopped to short third man
punched back to the bowler
Cook waits for this and places it out to deep cover
can't beat midwicket, just three runs off the over, better for India
very full and Cook plays an ungainly swing down to long on
inside edge to short fine-leg
big full toss outside off stump, Bell swings hard through the on side but straight to long-on, he missed out there
cut to deep cover
goes with the turn, cuts quite straight and cover gets a hand on it
uses his feet, makes it into a near-yorker as Bell drives out to deep cover...Zaheer is slow to the ball and Bell is quick with the running
can't beat Yuvraj off his own bowling
pitched outside leg stump and Cook works towards square leg
outside leg stump now to the right-hander, Bell picks out deep square-leg
quicker and flatter from Yuvraj, cuts it past short third-man and there's enough pace on the ball to reach the boundary...welcome boundary for Cook
turned off the pad out to deep square-leg, Cook is kept to a single
reverse sweep from Bell - not sure why - goes square on the off side for a single, less effort would have brought equal reward straight down the ground. That's drinks
cut through the covers off the back foot
a leave from Cook, in the 36th over, outside off stump
driven firmly towards Zaheer, who gets a hand on it and mid-off picks up
forced to backward point
down the pitch, good intent, and pull through midwicket...Robin Uthappa on the fence doesn't pick up cleanly
cut down to third man, placed well enough for another couple
punched firmly back to Yuvraj
turned through square leg
very full on the pads, turned wide of short fine-leg
uses his feet, frees his arms and goes over cover, long-off keeps them to two
into the leg side, ticking the score over but they can start expanding their stroke play now
pushed down to long on
played to backward point
tight line from Zaheer, on off stump and Cook can only defend straight down the pitch
top shot, low full toss from Zaheer and Cook times it superbly through midwicket and it's timed too well for long-on to get around
uses his feet again, but works straight to midwicket this time
worked off his pads down to fine leg
deft shot, good use of the wrists to guide the ball from outside off stump past Dhoni and down to third man
round the wicket, squirted off a thick outside edge through point
more good footwork, placed in the air through the covers and out to Agarkar on the cover fence to bring up England's 200
driven back to the bowler
charges down the pitch, but can't time a full toss as he picks out cover
goes for the cut but doesn't make contact
can't find the gaps, backward point fields
what a way to go to 99, flicked over midwicket and away to the boundary...he's played very well
there's his century, what a moment, driven through the covers and raises his bat all around The Rose Bowl and takes off his helmet to savour the moment...comes off 122 balls
driven down to long off
carved through point, Cook can really free his arms now
played off the back foot to backward point
driven towards long-off, the placement is good and Bell comes back for two
the attempted slower ball but it ends up as a full toss on leg stump and Bell gently flicks past the fielder at short fine leg, that was at 66mph, four easy runs
short of a length outside off stump, defended on the back foot towards point
too short and too wide outside off stump, Bell sits on the back foot and cuts through cover point
full length delivery on leg stump, Cook misses the flick and gets hit on the pad outside leg
full ball on middle stump, Bell chips it down to long-on for a single
Bell takes two steps down the pitch and drives straight past RP Singh to Zaheer at long-off, Zaheer's throw was hopeless and the batsmen run an overthrow
Bell triees to nudge a slower ball towards third man but misses
played with soft hands towards point for a single
bowled him! Cook tries to heave a full ball from outside off on the leg side but gets an inside edge on to off stump, RP Singh leaps in joy but Cook's batted very well for his maiden ODI hundred
short of a length outside off stump, Pietersen lets it go
short of a length outside off stump, Pietersen strides forward and drives through cover for  a single to get off the mark

a half-volley on leg stump, Pietersen flicks firmly through midwicket, he beats the fielder in the infield and he really shouldn't have beaten Gambhir in the deep who makes a poor dive on the boundary
driven on the front foot to mid-off
short ball on middle and leg, Pietersen gets on top of the bounce and pulls down to fine leg
short of a length on off and middle stump, Bell moves back and drives to long-on, Pietersen runs the first hard and sprints through for the second
punched off the back foot towards cover
a nice friendly full toss on middle stump, that was either the attempted slower ball or the attempted yorker, Pietersen misses out and hits it straight to midwicket
good length delivery cramps Bell for room as he tries to step down the track, he ends up defending it back to the bowler
full ball on off stump, Bell leans forward and drives to long-off
good length delivery on off stump, driven off the back foot to long-off
short and wide outside off stump, Bell reaches out for it and cuts but can't get it past Karthik who dives to make the save at point
Pietersen steps towards the off side and drives powerfully to Yuvraj who is at long-off
good length on middle and off stump, Bell is caught on the crease and he defends back to the bowler
slower ball on off stump, Pietersen leans forward and drives to long-off
he gets there with a flick off the pads to fine leg, 101 off 100 balls and he thrilled, he's paced the innings beautifully
driven to long-on for a single
that's a golf swing, Pietersen stood in his crease and lofted a full delivery over midwicket, the ball bounces just inside the boundary
full toss flicked behind square for  a single
too full outside off stump, Bell pushes the ball towards mid-off for a single
starts off with a full toss that Bell gently pushes down the ground for one
Pietersen backs away towards leg side, Tendulkar follows him but strays too far down, Pietersen uses the pace of the ball and glances it to the fine-leg boundary
driven inside out through extra cover for two more
driven to long-off on the front foot for a single
full toss on middle stump, Bell makes room by backing away and drives to long off
quicker delivery outside off, Pietersen tries to cut but misses
Bell moves towards the offside and chips a full ball over midwicket, Pietersen wants the strike and Bell settles for one
full delivery on middle and off stump, driven firmly but straight to cover
Pietersen backs away towards leg, giving Zaheer full view of the stumps, he drives a good length ball to extra cover for the single
full ball outside off stump, Bell tries to squueze it past point but misses
Bell backs away towards leg and then moves towards the off side once again, he flicks a full ball over midwicket for two more
Bell moves towards off and flicks a ball from outside off stump through square leg, two more to England
starts off with the yorker outside off, Pietersen tries to make room and plays it behind point
Bell backs away and drives a good-length ball to cover, all the fielders are on the edge of the circle and they scurry through for the single
Pietersen leans forward and lofts a good length ball down to long-off, Karthik is a little slow in getting to the ball and the batsmen run two
Pietersen moves quickly towards the leg side and drives powerfully through cover, Gambhir mops up on the boundary
tight line and length on middle and off, Pietersen drives to long-off
Bell moves his front foot out of the way and swats a fullish delivery to long-on
short ball on middle and leg stump, Bell moves towards square leg and pulls for a single
full toss on middle stump, Pietersen leans forward and flicks through midwicket for  a single
Bell backs away towards leg side and Zaheer bowls a yorker outside off stump, intelligent bowling
short ball outside off stump, Bell backs away and plays a tennis-forehand like shot over cover
Bell makes room and drives inside out through extra cover for four, he's placed that superbly and with a lot of power as well
slower ball outside off stump, Bell tries to slash it through point but gets an edge down to third man
slower ball and the length is short, Pietersen pulls through midwicket
full toss outside off stump, driven on the front foot to long-off
Bell tries to make room to smash it through cover but gets an inside edge past his stumps, Dhoni dives to his left to collect it
Bell moves towards the offside and scoops a leg-stump ball down to the fine-leg boundary, excellent improvisation
full toss on middle stump, Bell drives the ball to Yuvraj at long-on
Pietersen stands his ground and lofts a full ball down Tendulkar at long-off

inn2.comm: good start, outside off stump and some movement back into Ganguly who plays a loose drive and is beaten on the inside edge
Ganguly is away, an inside edge into the leg side
on middle and leg, worked through midwicket with a nice turn of the wrists
comes forward, the ball holds its line outside off stump and takes a thick outside edge down to third man
back of a length, going across Ganguly who plays out to backward point
half volley outside off stump, Ganguly drives but Bell makes a tumbling save at cover
down the leg side and Anderson starts with a wide, no leeway for bowlers in one-day cricket
on line this time, forced off the back foot to cover
on off stump, Tendulkar very correct and defends towards mid-off
drifting down the leg side again, takes the pad this time and beats Matt Prior's dive...the ball beats Stuart Broad into the fine-leg boundary, no swing for Anderson
positive forward stride from Tendulkar, finds backward point
outside off stump, Tendulkar happy to let this one go...no hint of movement
top shot, Tendulkar at his best, plays at the top of the bounce and drives square off the back foot on the off side and it raced away...good start for India
tight to Ganguly's body, defended down to mid-on
outside off stump, angled down to third man

early breakthrough for England, and Monty Panesar has pulled off a run-out. Tendulkar drove wide of mid-off, but didn't time it and Panesar made a good sliding save, got his throw away quickly to Matt Prior. Ganguly was coming back for a second, but Tendulkar wasn't interested and Ganguly was caught a couple of inches short.
defended back to Broad
solid drive straight at extra cover, but a silly throw from Pietersen gifts India a single...sloppy fielding straight after Monty's brilliant work
played past the on side of the stumps, compact drive straight at the fielder
unconvincing prod, towards backward point but they scamper a single
down the leg side again from Anderson, pitched in the foot holes and spat through to Prior who nearly took a blow in the face
big appeal, Anderson gets one to nip back off the pitch and takes Tendulkar on the pads, but Mark Benson says it's sliding down leg side
defended towards backward point
good line and good pace, on off stump and Tendulkar defends back to Anderson
another sweet back-foot drive from Tendulkar, but straight to the man on the edge of the circle at cover
slightly fuller, Tendulkar comes onto the front foot and drives...again straight at cover, as Anderson hits 90mph
on middle and off, played with a straight bat towards mid-on
outside off stump, chopped away towards Collingwood at backward point
full outside off stump and driven solidly to mid-off
on off stump, keeps Gambhir defending and this one goes to backward point
touch straighter and Gambhir works it off his hips down to long leg
on middle and off, Tendulkar defends and the ball hits Gambhir to prevent any runs
good line, Gambhir lets it go through to Prior
nearly found the edge, angling across Gambhir who is drawn into a defensive push
testing over, Gambhir opts to leave as Anderson again registers 90mph
little wider on this occasion, a more comfortable leave alone
this is wide and short enough to tempt a drive from Gambhir, but he picks out backward point...five dot balls

the pressure pays off, Gambhir goes for a flat-footed drive against a fuller ball, but only succeeds in getting a thin edge through to Prior. Anderson deserved that, it's his 100th ODI wicket, and England are well on top
punchy drive to mid-off, how expansive can Tendulkar be after the early wickets?
close for England, nips back at Tendulkar and goes between bat and pad...England up for a catch and lbw, but there was no bat and it was too high, excellent bowling though
flicks the pad down the leg side
long half volley, but Tendulkar picks out England's fielding star- Panesar - at mid-off
he can't find the gap, Bopara picks up the back-foot drive at cover
another cracking delivery, more late movement into Tendulkar who is taken on the pad...huge appeal from Broad but Billy Doctrove right says it is going over the top
drifts onto middle and leg, looked like he was trying for a repeat of the ball that bowled him at The Oval, but Dravid threads through midwicket to open his account
forced off the back foot towards mid-off, they go for a quick single and it's well judged
worked off the stumps to midwicket
Anderson is hitting the deck hard today, Dravid defends into the leg side
goes for the yorker, it's on target but Dravid is quickly down to it and digs out to the off side
on off stump, Dravid defends to backward point
worked into the leg side, Bell from midwicket dives and keeps them to a single
flicked off the hip down to long leg, where sub fielder Owais Shah (on for Anderson) does the fielding
punched towards mid-off, Tendulkar goes for a quick single and Panesar lets himself down as he fumbles and allows them back for a second
flowing drive into the covers, but it's a tightly packed off side and it goes to cover
uses his strong wrists, flicks a straight delivery to midwicket
huge shout for lbw, but there's a big inside edge into the pads from Tendulkar as he tries to drive and the excitement doesn't last
flicked to midwicket, a good save from Bopara prevents any runs
jumps to get on top of the bounce and defended to backward point
angles down to third man, it's tough going for the Indian batsmen
driven to the man at short point, the bat turns in his hands and the ball almost carried to Cook
an expansive drive takes the inside just past the stumps and down to fine leg...Anderson v Tendulkar has been good this summer
Dravid is squared up and plays to backward point
short of a length outside off stump, Tendulkar waits on the back foot and slices the ball behind point down to third man
good length delivery nipping back into Dravid from outside off stump, he gets on to the back foot and dabs it with soft hands on the off side for a single
just a fraction short outside off stump, Tendulkar gets on to the back foot and drives past Panesar at mid-off, Panesar chases well and saves the boundary
good length ball on off stump, Dravid gets behind the line of the ball and defends on the front foot
full ball on middle stump, Dravid leans forward and drives to Flintoff who is rather straight at mid-off
good length ball angles into Dravid who waits for it to come to him and defends on the off side

Anderson surprises Yuvraj with a sharp bouncer, Yuvraj jumps up, takes his eyes off the ball and defends awkwardly

defended on the back foot back to the bowler
played to third man for  a single

left alone once again outside the off stump
